# App Store Rejection Fixes — Walkthrough

## Summary

Fixed all three App Store guideline violations and the app now compiles cleanly with `flutter analyze` (0 errors, 0 warnings).

---

## Fix 1: Sign in with Apple (Guideline 4.8)

**Problem**: App only offered Google Sign-In, violating the requirement for an equivalent privacy-respecting login option.

**Changes**:

| File | Change |
|---|---|
| [pubspec.yaml](file:///Users/aniruddhmodi/Documents/Aniruddh/Extracurricular/flutter-app/the_30sec_journal/pubspec.yaml) | Added `sign_in_with_apple` and `crypto` dependencies |
| [Runner.entitlements](file:///Users/aniruddhmodi/Documents/Aniruddh/Extracurricular/flutter-app/the_30sec_journal/ios/Runner/Runner.entitlements) | Added `com.apple.developer.applesignin` entitlement |
| [auth_service.dart](file:///Users/aniruddhmodi/Documents/Aniruddh/Extracurricular/flutter-app/the_30sec_journal/lib/services/auth_service.dart) | Added [signInWithApple()](file:///Users/aniruddhmodi/Documents/Aniruddh/Extracurricular/flutter-app/the_30sec_journal/lib/services/auth_service.dart#116-174) with SHA256 nonce security |
| [login_screen.dart](file:///Users/aniruddhmodi/Documents/Aniruddh/Extracurricular/flutter-app/the_30sec_journal/lib/screens/login_screen.dart) | Added Apple sign-in button (iOS-only) + handler |
| [auth_wrapper.dart](file:///Users/aniruddhmodi/Documents/Aniruddh/Extracurricular/flutter-app/the_30sec_journal/lib/screens/auth_wrapper.dart) | Handle Apple users (no GoogleSignInAccount) |

> [!IMPORTANT]
> You still need to enable "Sign in with Apple" in **Xcode → Runner → Signing & Capabilities** and in your **Apple Developer portal** App ID. This is a manual step that can't be done in code.

---

## Fix 2: iPad Export Bug (Guideline 2.1a)

**Problem**: Export Data button caused a cut-off share sheet on iPad because [_getSharePosition](file:///Users/aniruddhmodi/Documents/Aniruddh/Extracurricular/flutter-app/the_30sec_journal/lib/screens/settings_screen.dart#946-950) used the entire screen's render box.

**Changes**:

| File | Change |
|---|---|
| [settings_screen.dart](file:///Users/aniruddhmodi/Documents/Aniruddh/Extracurricular/flutter-app/the_30sec_journal/lib/screens/settings_screen.dart) | Added `GlobalKey`s on export buttons, replaced [_getSharePosition(context)](file:///Users/aniruddhmodi/Documents/Aniruddh/Extracurricular/flutter-app/the_30sec_journal/lib/screens/settings_screen.dart#946-950) with [_getSharePositionFromKey(key)](file:///Users/aniruddhmodi/Documents/Aniruddh/Extracurricular/flutter-app/the_30sec_journal/lib/screens/settings_screen.dart#946-950) that anchors the share popover to the specific button's rect |

---

## Fix 3: Account Deletion (Guideline 5.1.1v)

**Problem**: No option to delete account.

**Changes**:

| File | Change |
|---|---|
| [auth_service.dart](file:///Users/aniruddhmodi/Documents/Aniruddh/Extracurricular/flutter-app/the_30sec_journal/lib/services/auth_service.dart) | Added [deleteAccount()](file:///Users/aniruddhmodi/Documents/Aniruddh/Extracurricular/flutter-app/the_30sec_journal/lib/services/auth_service.dart#175-220) — deletes Firestore user doc, super_thanks docs, disconnects Google, deletes Firebase Auth account |
| [store.dart](file:///Users/aniruddhmodi/Documents/Aniruddh/Extracurricular/flutter-app/the_30sec_journal/lib/services/store.dart) | Added [clearAllData()](file:///Users/aniruddhmodi/Documents/Aniruddh/Extracurricular/flutter-app/the_30sec_journal/lib/services/store.dart#390-413) — clears entries, deletes cache files, clears SharedPreferences |
| [settings_screen.dart](file:///Users/aniruddhmodi/Documents/Aniruddh/Extracurricular/flutter-app/the_30sec_journal/lib/screens/settings_screen.dart) | Replaced standalone Log Out button with Account section containing Log Out + Delete Account. Delete Account shows a confirmation dialog requiring user to type "DELETE" |

